eset here. These members disappeared without even saying goodbye. <br><br>Experiencing this, I came up with my own guild concept and went about trying to find people who liked it. And as time progressed, i found it VERY DIFFICULT to form a new guild.<br>Reasons for this is, IMHO, many citizens of Norrath experienced the same as i did so joining an established guild is easier because the friends you made in them look like they are going to stay.<br><br>There are other reasons why guilds fail also of course...poor leadership, poor guild structure, ect.<br><br>What i did learn from my own experiences, and observing the rise and fall of various guilds, is that reputation is very important. Word travels fast on this server of the actions of one. If one of your guildmates does something dishonorable, the whole guild can be judged for it. Sometimes the scope of the judgement is small sometimes not....but as the number of offenses add up, the guild definetely gets a bad name.<br><br>When a guild has a bad name...they have a harder time recruiting those members that they desire, planning multi guild events that include them becomes harder, and can possibly get to the point that members of a group will not allow a player to join simply because of their guild tag. (Dhugal personally associates his guild tag to be synonymous his own name and so goes out of his way to correct wrongs because he wants others to respect it, whether they are in another guild or not.)<br><br>This makes it important to the leaders, if they care about the longevity of their guild, to try to make right what one of their numbers wronged. Personally, I find nothing wrong with this and i highly doubt there is a guild out there that hasnt done some damage control if they accept any members who they hadn't known for a decent amount of time before allowing them into their guild. And even more so, if a player steps up to correct a wrong that is done to you due to another player, i think that is commendable and speak loudly of the goodness of that guild. Not one of us is perfect, nor any guild for that matter. <br><br>So what i am trying to say is, appreciate the fact that guilded people honor their guild name when they do this, and even more because when they do, they are also helping you with the problem that you are having at the moment and they DID NOT HAVE to. If you have a beef with someone who is in a guild, i highly recommend that you take it up with their leaders...you may come out possibly more ahead than you would be if the problem had never occurred.<br><br>Dhugal Forgefyre<br>Society of Valor Councilman <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxsatyrx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xsatyrx</A> at: 1/8/02 9:58:11 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urhaelofthevoid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhael of the Void</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Servant of the Void</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/8/02 10:11:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild Name Damage Control</span><hr size=1> We may not see eye to eye on F Vie, but here we are in agreement.  I value the Tag above my head, and consider it an honour to wear it.  If any have issue with the Indigo Void, have no fear in contacting me. I can't imadgine any of my folks upseting any one (except high elves, and they don't count =) but if they do, let me know!  I 'd like to think we have a rep of being fair minded good players, and I'd like to keep it that way.<br><br> <p>Rhael T'LehrIndigo Void</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umorgenayanamii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morgen Ayanamii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/8/02 11:59:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild Name Damage Control</span><hr size=1> My personal policy is not to blame one bad apple on the rest of the barrel, so to speak.<br><br>I have one or two people I really don't want to have much to do with.  I haven't even /ignored them, so far.  I have encountered one guild which seems to have a bizarre mix of folks - My encounters with folk from that guild have both high positive and high negative ratings, very dynamic.<br><br>There is a tendancy to be wary after a bad experience with someone.  We all have it to one degree or another.   But if other folk in a guild, including the officers of course, at least *try* to deal with a specific case, then a good faith effort can go far to alleviating any long term considerations of dealing with that group of folk, even if an individual there becomes a no-no.<br><br>But it's impossible to screen out all the loonies, no matter how hard you try.  And if you try too hard, you won't ever recruit to begin with.<br><br>Morgen Ayanamii, speaking for herself<br>Circle of Sisters <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uelsbetsquishytoes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>elsbet squishytoes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Grey</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 6:20:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild Name Damage Control</span><hr size=1> I travel this world with the name of my guild in tow.  Whereever I go, the name of &lt;Starspun&gt; follows.  This guild medallion, by decree, is fully visible at all times by anyone, and I be proud to wear it.  I am blessed with a good family, that sees things much the same way as I, and I am embarrassed of none of them.<br><br>I do me best to be honest, honorable, and consistent in what I do in this world.  I strive to ensure that my family and guild name remain in good favor.  I can only be one person in this world, and I hope to be the best person that I can.<br><br>Elsbet Squishytoes<br>           awake much too late <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhelmgest.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Helmgest</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 11:23:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild Name Damage Control</span><hr size=1> Not to hijack the thread’s central idea (which everyone seems to be violently in agreement with anyway), but are guilds having a tough time recruiting?<br><br>Some, like F&amp;F and Clan Were, have level restrictions on them and so limit their applicants, but most of the others that I am familiar with do not.  In the 20-30 level range, there are a fair number of unguilded folks out there.  <br><br>My regular hunting partner and I have been looking for a guild to call home for a while, especially since finding groups is becoming less easy.  Surprisingly, this has not been a simple task – many of the guilds we are interested in (won’t mention names) are insular enough that it’s tough to get to know the members.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uaeonii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeonii</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://aeonii.freeservers.com/images/colors.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 12:19:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild Name Damage Control</span><hr size=1> :is curious as to what provoked this thread...<br><br>All of Immortal Kindred live to make playing experiences a postive for all players, ours or not.  I hope that each time any of you come across one of our own, that it is a postive experience.  (Well, at least within reason...  I have been known to /gasp when I see dark elves and Qued. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    )  Please let me or Brazzelbe know if you find anything different from one of our kindred.<br><br>Helmgest...  Check out the Guilds and Associations thread at the bottom of this site's homepage.  You may find some good information about guilds, and which one would be good for you.  Aye, we have hard times finding people to join, but we don't want to be a large guild, either.  Seems like most times when we find just the right player, we say, &quot;Too bad they have a tag already.&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br>All my best... <p><p align="center"><font color="#E1B500"><b><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=98751"><i><font size="2" color="#E1B500">ÆoniiElysium<br></font></i></a></b><a href="http://members.tripod.com/immortalkindred"><font size="1" color="#E1B500">~*~An Immortal Kindred ~*~</font></a></font></p><p align="center"><font size="1" color="#E1B500">Jyleel</font></p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uaeonii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeonii</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://aeonii.freeservers.com/images/colors.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/9/02 12:20:35 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufeneant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feneant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 224<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 12:32:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild Name Damage Control</span><hr size=1> Recruiting isn't the problem, the problem is a lot of low level peeps see the big guilds and think they are the only good ones out there and they have level restrictions.  I'm in a pretty good guild and we have no level restrictions whatsoever, we've even started recruiting in newbie zones to give them a chance.<br><br>I see it like this, if you apply for a guild and they say 'your too low' and you stop searching and wait to re-apply, then if I was an officer, I wouldn't recruit you.  But if you are a level 3-4 and a guild says your too low but you keep looking, many guilds will take you in.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxsatyrx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xsatyrx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 12:59:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild Name Damage Control</span><hr size=1> Aye, in actuality, Society of Valor is having no problems find members. We are strong and prospering now....but getting the first 10 for formation was a Biotch! Now there is no problem at all....what provoked this thread...well i was slightly disturbed about a post one made after i was given Kudos by another. It is my opinion that even if one of us were given Kudos for something that we find no big deal, we pass it up. This person did not, but gave reason why Kudos werent necessary for my actions. I personally appreciated the fact the the Kudos Bearer would post his appreciation as he did because it was way out of my way. Did i expect Kudos?...No, but being i recieved them felt good and i enjoyed it. And the other poster lessened it by his post...so i thought id make a post here to explain that. My post main reason seems to be lost in the text...which is simply the guild leaders are not required to fix their guildmembers screwups. and if one goes out of his way to correct a wrong...it would be wise to give him respect. To those who feel no respect is needed...give me advance warning and i wont waste my time. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxsatyrx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xsatyrx</A> at: 1/9/02 1:11:19 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhelmgest.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Helmgest</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 1:22:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild Name Damage Control</span><hr size=1> &gt;I see it like this, if you apply for a guild and they say 'your<br>&gt; too low' and you stop searching and wait to re-apply, then if<br>&gt; I was an officer, I wouldn't recruit you. <br><br>I can’t seem to understand that statement.  May I ask why you would be unwilling to recruit him?<br><br>It seems to me that if someone really likes your guild, asks to join, is told that they are too low, levels up and asks again, they would be the perfect addition.  Wouldn’t they be a better choice than someone who joins another guild until they are the appropriate level and then jumps ship?  And what is the difference between that person and the guy who IS the appropriate level and asks to join for the first time?<br><br>&gt;Check out the Guilds and Associations thread at the bottom<br>&gt; of this site's homepage. You may find some good<br>&gt; information about guilds, and which one would be good for<br>&gt; you. <br><br>That and Firiona-Via.com were my first stops when I started looking a few weeks back.  Great resources.  I’m pretty clear on where I want to be, which is why I didn’t want to name names.  I didn’t mean my post above to be a cry for help (re-reading it, it seems that way though), just a statement on how surprisingly difficult it has been to contact the guild in question, find officers, etc.<br><br>I was just struck by one of the points in this thread which seemed to indicate that recruiting was an issue – again, it seems to me that about 50% of the 20-30 crowd (prime guilding age, I reckon) are unaffiliated, so I found that to be 